This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a new method for improving the performance of the DDPG algorithm. It also involves training neural networks to learn how to run, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of an ensemble of actors and critics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
